UYO  – Wife of Governor Udom Em­manuel’s preferred successor, Mrs. Patience Umo Eno, has come public to declare her hus­band, “A Golden Boy.” The gold-skinned Commis­sioner for Lands and Water Resources, Mr. Umo Eno, had since presentation to the public by Governor Udom Emmanu­el as his preferred successor been declared unsuitable by a section of the public to occupy the number one public office in the state for being an “albino.” Some have gone as far as gathering pictures of albinos across ages and gender on so­cial media platforms, present­ing them as soon to be leaders of the state. Again, Ovrode Community Shuts Down Ughelli/Asaba Expressway For… Ido Aiyegunle Monarch Warns Land Grabbers To Steer Clear In a video clip which cir­culated online on Sunday, the expectant first lady, during a consultation worship with All Nations Christian Church in Eket on Sunday said, “My husband is very special and unique; they call him albino but I say he’s my golden boy. Let me tell you something, my husband’s colour especially his hair colour is what some ladies are paying to have.” Many have given various shades of interpretations to Mrs Eno’s public outburst. While some thought it was too early to show off herself; others have applauded her for demon­strating such “home front” sup­port for her husband. Whatever the case may have been, “My Golden Boy” is currently trending on various social media platforms.